"Official GitHub Repository" means the GitHub repository designated by the
copyright holder as the official source location for the Software, currently
yiyousiow000814/XAUUSD-Calendar-Agent.

"GitHub Fork" means a fork of the Official GitHub Repository created using
GitHub's standard fork functionality.

"Public Sharing" means making the Software (or any portion, copy, or modified
version of it) available to the public or to persons beyond those you directly
and privately communicate with, including (without limitation) posting or
uploading it to:
(a) social media or content platforms (e.g., Facebook, Instagram, Xiaohongshu,
    Reddit);
(b) forums, public chat rooms, or public file-sharing services;
(c) public code hosting services (e.g., GitHub/GitLab) or package registries;
(d) app stores, download sites, or any publicly accessible website.

For clarity: Public Sharing does not include accessing the Software via the
Official GitHub Repository on GitHub, including creating or maintaining a
GitHub Fork on GitHub, solely for Personal, Non-Commercial Research.

"Public Promotion" means publicly advertising, promoting, or marketing the
Software, including by posting its name, links, screenshots, demo videos, or
descriptions of the Software on any publicly accessible platform, website, or
service (including those listed under Public Sharing).

For clarity: Public Promotion does not include creating or maintaining a
GitHub Fork on GitHub solely for Personal, Non-Commercial Research.

"Private Recommendation" means telling another Individual about the Software
through a private, person-to-person channel (e.g., email or direct message)
and, if desired, sending them a link to an official download/source location
provided by the copyright holder, without providing any copy of the Software
